Then beginning with respectful mention of Augustus he turned to the victorioe and triumphs of Tiberius, recounting with especial praise the brilliant achieve- ments he had accomplished with those legions in the Germanias, Then he eulogised the unanimity of Italy, the loyalty of the Gauls; no mutiny or strife anywhere.
